Minnie Dlamini-Jones's brother Khosini has died after being in ICU for several weeks, the family's spokesperson confirmed on Friday. This comes after Khosini suffered from a brain aneurysm earlier this month, which led to him being admitted. The Dlamini family spokesperson Tlhogi Ngwato confirmed Khosini's death to IOL Entertainment. "It is with great sadness we confirm our beloved Khosini passed away yesterday afternoon, after suffering a ruptured brain aneurysm which placed him on life support for 23 days. "He passed peacefully at hospital, surrounded by the love of his family. In this time of grief we ask for privacy and the opportunity to celebrate him. "Khosini is survived by his parents Queen and Jabulani Dlamini, and siblings Maphe and Minenhle", said Ngwato. Fans of the "Becoming Mrs Jones"Â star shared their condolences on Twitter.     Minnie Dlaminiâ€™s younger brother has died. Yoh Iâ€™m so heartbroken I couldnâ€™t imagine losing my little brother ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ğŸ’” yhini my God!     @MinnieDlamini where do I even begin Minnie ,I am so sorry about your brother , he was truly amazing , humble sweet , respectful , sorrry for your loss     Minnieâ€™s brother? ğŸ’”ğŸ’”     I'm really sorry for your loss ğŸ˜­ğŸ’”deepest condolences to the family and friends. Ooouh Minnie i can only imagine     Condolences to you and the Dlaminis. ğŸ™ğŸ¾Wasnâ€™t it too early to share on Social Media though? Iâ€™m not telling you how to mourn, donâ€™t get me wrong. Angilwi...     Condolences to you and the Dlaminis. ğŸ™ğŸ¾Wasnâ€™t it too early to share on Social Media though? Iâ€™m not telling you how to mourn, donâ€™t get me wrong. Angilwi...